==Scottish Gaelic==
'''gu''' {{IPA|ɡu}}
===Adverb===
# Makes an adverb when placed in front of an adjective
* ''Tha mi gu math.'' I am (doing) well.
===Preposition===
# [[to]]; almgamates with pronouns to form thugam(sa), thugad(sa), thuige(san), thuice(se), thugainn(e), thugaibh(se), and thuca(san).
* ''Chuir mi litir gu mo phàrantan.'' I sent a letter to my parents.
[[Category:Scots Gaelic prepositions]]
